EU Grants Sierra Leone 16.5 Million Euros to Improve Governance

-- B y   S i l a s   G b a n d i a
-- 
2011-06-24T15:30:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-24/eu-grants-sierra-leone-16-5-million-euros-to-improve-governance.html
The European Union agreed to grant
 Sierra Leone  16.5 million euros ($23.4 million) to help improve
governance in the West African nation and develop environmental
protection.  About 10.5 million euros will help better standards in the
civil service, while 4 million euros will support the Sierra
Leone Environmental Protection Agency, the EU delegation to
Sierra Leone said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Silas Gbandia in Freetown via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
AntonySguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 